---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - TimeHopper">
    <div class="legal-container">
        <div class="header">
            <a href="/index.html" class="logo">
                <img src="/images/icon48.png" alt="TimeHopper Logo" style="width: 32px; height: 32px;">
                TimeHopper
            </a>
        </div>

        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p>Last updated: January 29, 2026</p>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>TimeHopper ("we", "our", or "us") is a Chrome Extension designed to help you manage time zones and schedule
                meetings. We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal data.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Data We Collect</h2>
            <p>TimeHopper accesses the minimum amount of data necessary to function:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Calendar Data:</strong> We access your Google Calendar events strictly to display them to you in
                    the extension popup and to provide meeting notifications. This data is fetched directly from Google's
                    APIs and is stored locally in your browser. We do not transmit this data to any external servers.</li>
                <li><strong>User Preferences:</strong> using Chrome Storage, we save your settings (such as selected time
                    zones, working hours, and notification preferences).</li>
                <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> We use aggregated, anonymous analytics (via <strong>Amplitude</strong>) to understand feature
                    usage and improve the product. This data does not contain personally identifiable information (PII) or
                    calendar details. No calendar content is ever sent to analytics.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Limited Use Disclosure</h2>
            <p>TimeHopper's use and transfer of information received from Google APIs to any other app will adhere to the <a href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy" target="_blank">Google API Services User Data Policy</a>, including the Limited Use requirements.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>No AI training</h2>
            <p>We believe your data belongs to you. We <strong>do not</strong> use any information from your Google Calendar to train Large Language Models (LLMs) or any other artificial intelligence systems.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Data Protection Disclosures</h2>
            <p>To provide maximum transparency for our users and for Google OAuth review, we explicitly disclose the following:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Limited Use:</strong> TimeHopper's use and transfer of information received from Google APIs to any other app will adhere to the <a href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy" target="_blank">Google API Services User Data Policy</a>, including the Limited Use requirements.</li>
                <li><strong>Local Storage:</strong> All Google Calendar event data is stored exclusively in your browser's local storage (via Chrome Storage API). This data never touches our servers.</li>
                <li><strong>No Third-Party Sharing of Calendar Data:</strong> We do not share, sell, or transmit your Google Calendar event content to any third parties, including our analytics provider (Amplitude).</li>
                <li><strong>Minimum Permissions:</strong> We only request <code>calendar.readonly</code> to display your events and <code>userinfo.email</code> to identify your connected account.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>How We Use Your Data</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>To display your upcoming schedule and time blocks.</li>
                <li>To provide desktop notifications for upcoming meetings.</li>
                <li>To calculate time zone overlaps for team coordination.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
            <p>We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal information to outside parties. As noted above, we use Amplitude for anonymous product analytics, and Google APIs for fetching your calendar data directly.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at <a
                    href="mailto:support@timehopper.app">support@timehopper.app</a>.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>

<style>
    .legal-container {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 40px 20px;
    }

    .header {
        padding-bottom: 30px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
        margin-bottom: 30px;
    }

    .logo {
        font-size: 24px;
        font-weight: 800;
        color: #333;
        text-decoration: none;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 10px;
    }

    h1 {
        font-size: 2.5em;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
        color: #2c3e50;
    }

    h2 {
        color: #2c3e50;
        margin-top: 30px;
    }

    .section {
        margin-bottom: 30px;
    }
</style>
